---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalLayout from '../../components/layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { getBaseUrl, createUrl } from '../../utils/url';

const base = getBaseUrl();
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy | AUXO Data Labs"
  description="Learn about how AUXO Data Labs uses cookies and tracking technologies on our website to improve your experience and analyze usage."
>
  <div class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <LegalLayout
        title="Cookie Policy"
        lastUpdated="January 15, 2025"
        effectiveDate="January 1, 2025"
        summary="This Cookie Policy explains how AUXO Data Labs uses cookies and similar tracking technologies on our website. We use cookies to enhance your browsing experience, analyze website performance, and deliver relevant content."
      >
        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div class="mb-8 p-6 bg-accent-green/5 border border-accent-green/20 rounded-lg">
          <h2 class="!mt-0">What Are Cookies?</h2>
          <p>
            Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device (computer, tablet, smartphone) when you visit a website.
          </p>
          <p>
            They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently, provide analytics insights, and deliver a personalized experience. Cookies can remember your preferences, track your browsing behavior, and help website owners understand how visitors use their sites.
          </p>
          <p>
            This Cookie Policy should be read in conjunction with our <a href={createUrl('legal/privacy-policy')}>Privacy Policy</a>, which provides more details about how we collect and use your personal information.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2>1. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
        <p>We use different categories of cookies on the AUXO Data Labs website. Here's what each type does:</p>

        <h3>1.1 Strictly Necessary Cookies</h3>
        <div class="my-4 p-4 bg-card border-l-4 border-accent-green rounded-r-lg transition-colors">
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Purpose:</strong> Essential for the website to function properly</p>
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Can you disable them?</strong> No - these are required for basic functionality</p>
          <p class="!mb-0 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Legal Basis:</strong> Legitimate interest (necessary for website operation)</p>
        </div>
        <p><strong>What they do:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Enable basic website functionality (page navigation, form submission)</li>
          <li>Maintain security and prevent fraudulent activity</li>
          <li>Remember your cookie consent preferences</li>
          <li>Ensure secure areas of the website remain protected</li>
          <li>Load balance and distribute traffic across servers</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Cookie Name</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">cookie_consent</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Stores your cookie preferences</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">1 year</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">session_id</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Maintains session state</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Session (deleted when browser closes)</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3>1.2 Performance & Analytics Cookies</h3>
        <div class="my-4 p-4 bg-card border-l-4 border-accent-green rounded-r-lg transition-colors">
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Purpose:</strong> Help us understand how visitors interact with our website</p>
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Can you disable them?</strong> Yes - these are optional</p>
          <p class="!mb-0 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Legal Basis:</strong> Consent (you can opt-out)</p>
        </div>
        <p><strong>What they do:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Collect information about how you use our website (pages visited, time spent, clicks)</li>
          <li>Help us improve website performance and user experience</li>
          <li>Identify technical issues and errors</li>
          <li>Understand which content is most valuable to visitors</li>
          <li>All data is aggregated and anonymized</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Cookie Name</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Provider</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">_ga</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Google Analytics</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Distinguishes unique visitors</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">2 years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">_ga_*</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Google Analytics 4</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Maintains session state and counts page views</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">2 years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">_gid</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Google Analytics</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Distinguishes users for daily tracking</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">24 hours</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">_gat</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Google Analytics</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Throttles request rate</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">1 minute</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3>1.3 Functional Cookies</h3>
        <div class="my-4 p-4 bg-card border-l-4 border-accent-green rounded-r-lg transition-colors">
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Purpose:</strong> Enable enhanced functionality and personalization</p>
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Can you disable them?</strong> Yes - but some features may not work properly</p>
          <p class="!mb-0 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Legal Basis:</strong> Consent or legitimate interest (depending on function)</p>
        </div>
        <p><strong>What they do:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Remember your preferences and settings (language, region, theme)</li>
          <li>Enable interactive tools (maturity assessment, calculators)</li>
          <li>Provide chat support functionality (if enabled)</li>
          <li>Remember form inputs to improve usability</li>
          <li>Personalize content based on your interests</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Cookie Name</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">user_preferences</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Stores UI preferences and settings</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">1 year</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">assessment_data</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Temporarily stores maturity assessment responses</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Session</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3>1.4 Marketing & Targeting Cookies</h3>
        <div class="my-4 p-4 bg-card border-l-4 border-accent-green rounded-r-lg transition-colors">
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Purpose:</strong> Deliver relevant advertising and measure campaign effectiveness</p>
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Can you disable them?</strong> Yes - these require your explicit consent</p>
          <p class="!mb-0 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">Legal Basis:</strong> Consent (opt-in required)</p>
        </div>
        <p><strong>What they do:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Track your browsing to build a profile of your interests</li>
          <li>Show you relevant ads on other websites (retargeting)</li>
          <li>Measure the effectiveness of marketing campaigns</li>
          <li>Prevent showing the same ad repeatedly (frequency capping)</li>
          <li>Share data with advertising networks (with your consent)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Cookie Name</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Provider</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">_fbp</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Facebook Pixel</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Tracks conversions and ad performance (if enabled)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">3 months</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-xs text-secondary transition-colors">li_sugr</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">LinkedIn Insight</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Supports LinkedIn advertising and analytics (if enabled)</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">30 days</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p class="text-sm text-secondary transition-colors italic">Note: Marketing cookies are only set if you provide explicit consent. We currently focus on B2B marketing through LinkedIn and professional channels.</p>

        <h2>2. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
        <p>Some cookies are placed by third-party services that appear on our website. We do not control these cookies, and you should check the third-party websites for more information.</p>

        <h3>2.1 Google Analytics</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Provider:</strong> Google LLC</li>
          <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Website analytics and performance monitoring</li>
          <li><strong>Data Collected:</strong> Pages visited, time on site, browser type, device type, referring URLs</li>
          <li><strong>Privacy Policy:</strong> <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a></li>
          <li><strong>Data Retention:</strong> 26 months (configurable)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 LinkedIn (Business Network)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Provider:</strong> LinkedIn Corporation</li>
          <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Professional networking, B2B advertising, conversion tracking</li>
          <li><strong>Data Collected:</strong> Profile information (if logged in), browsing behavior, interactions</li>
          <li><strong>Privacy Policy:</strong> <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Manage settings in your LinkedIn account</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.3 Social Media Embeds</h3>
        <p>When we embed content from social media platforms (LinkedIn posts, Twitter feeds), those platforms may set cookies. These include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Embedded company updates and professional content</li>
          <li><strong>Twitter/X:</strong> Social sharing and embedded tweets (if used)</li>
          <li><strong>YouTube:</strong> Embedded videos (using privacy-enhanced mode when possible)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Use Cookies</h2>
        <p>We use cookies for the following specific purposes:</p>

        <h3>3.1 Website Performance & Security</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Load Balancing:</strong> Distribute traffic across servers for optimal performance</li>
          <li><strong>Security Monitoring:</strong> Detect and prevent fraudulent activity, DDoS attacks</li>
          <li><strong>Error Detection:</strong> Identify and fix technical issues quickly</li>
          <li><strong>Session Management:</strong> Maintain your browsing session across pages</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 User Experience Enhancement</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Preference Storage:</strong> Remember your language, timezone, display settings</li>
          <li><strong>Form Assistance:</strong> Save partially completed forms so you don't lose progress</li>
          <li><strong>Interactive Tools:</strong> Enable maturity assessment and calculator functionality</li>
          <li><strong>Navigation Improvement:</strong> Track which pages are most/least used to optimize site structure</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.3 Analytics & Insights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Traffic Analysis:</strong> Understand visitor demographics, behavior, and engagement</li>
          <li><strong>Content Optimization:</strong> Identify which blog posts, case studies, and resources are most valuable</li>
          <li><strong>Conversion Tracking:</strong> Measure effectiveness of CTAs, forms, and lead magnets</li>
          <li><strong>A/B Testing:</strong> Test different page layouts and content to improve user experience</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.4 Marketing & Communication</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Campaign Attribution:</strong> Understand which marketing channels bring visitors to our site</li>
          <li><strong>Retargeting:</strong> Show relevant ads to previous visitors (with consent)</li>
          <li><strong>Lead Scoring:</strong> Identify high-intent prospects based on browsing behavior</li>
          <li><strong>Email Personalization:</strong> Customize email content based on website interactions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h2>

        <h3>4.1 Cookie Consent Management</h3>
        <p>When you first visit our website, you'll see a cookie consent banner that allows you to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Accept All Cookies:</strong> Consent to all cookie categories</li>
          <li><strong>Reject Non-Essential:</strong> Only allow strictly necessary cookies</li>
          <li><strong>Customize Settings:</strong> Choose which categories of cookies to enable</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can change your preferences at any time by clicking the "Cookie Settings" link in the footer of our website.</p>

        <h3>4.2 Browser Settings</h3>
        <p>All modern browsers allow you to manage cookies through their settings. You can:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Block All Cookies:</strong> Prevent any cookies from being stored</li>
          <li><strong>Block Third-Party Cookies:</strong> Allow only cookies from the website you're visiting</li>
          <li><strong>Delete Existing Cookies:</strong> Clear all cookies currently stored on your device</li>
          <li><strong>Set Exceptions:</strong> Allow cookies from specific websites only</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>How to manage cookies in popular browsers:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies and other site data</li>
          <li><strong>Mozilla Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
          <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
          <li><strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions → Cookies and site data</li>
          <li><strong>Brave:</strong> Settings → Shields → Cookies and other site data</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="my-6 p-4 bg-yellow-500/10 border border-yellow-500/30 rounded-lg">
          <p class="!mb-2"><strong>⚠️ Important Note:</strong></p>
          <p class="!mb-0">Blocking or deleting cookies may affect your ability to use certain features of our website. Essential cookies are required for basic functionality and cannot be disabled without affecting site performance.</p>
        </div>

        <h3>4.3 Opt-Out Tools & Resources</h3>
        <p>For more granular control, you can use industry opt-out tools:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics Opt-out:</strong> <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Browser Add-on</a></li>
          <li><strong>Your Online Choices (EU):</strong> <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Manage Ad Preferences</a></li>
          <li><strong>Network Advertising Initiative:</strong> <a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NAI Opt-out</a></li>
          <li><strong>Digital Advertising Alliance:</strong> <a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">WebChoices Tool</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.4 Mobile Devices</h3>
        <p>On mobile devices, you can control tracking through:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>iOS:</strong> Settings → Privacy → Tracking → Allow Apps to Request to Track (toggle off)</li>
          <li><strong>Android:</strong> Settings → Google → Ads → Opt out of Ads Personalization</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Cookie Lifespan</h2>
        <p>Cookies can be either session cookies or persistent cookies:</p>

        <h3>5.1 Session Cookies</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Duration:</strong> Temporary - deleted when you close your browser</li>
          <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Maintain your browsing session, shopping cart, form data</li>
          <li><strong>Example:</strong> session_id, assessment_data</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.2 Persistent Cookies</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Duration:</strong> Remain on your device for a set period (from 1 day to 2 years)</li>
          <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Remember preferences, track long-term behavior, analytics</li>
          <li><strong>Example:</strong> _ga (2 years), user_preferences (1 year)</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-6">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Category</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Typical Duration</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-accent-green transition-colors">Auto-Deletion</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Strictly Necessary</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Session to 1 year</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">When browser closes or after expiry</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Performance/Analytics</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">1 day to 2 years</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">After expiry period</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Functional</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Session to 1 year</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">After expiry or manual deletion</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-theme">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">Marketing/Targeting</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">30 days to 1 year</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-secondary transition-colors">After expiry or opt-out</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2>6. International Transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Some of our third-party service providers (e.g., Google Analytics, LinkedIn) are based outside the United Arab Emirates, which means cookies may result in data being transferred internationally. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place through:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) approved by regulators</li>
          <li>Adequacy decisions recognizing equivalent data protection</li>
          <li>Data Processing Agreements with all third-party providers</li>
          <li>Regular vendor security and compliance audits</li>
        </ul>
        <p>For more information, see our <a href={createUrl('legal/privacy-policy')}>Privacy Policy</a> section on International Data Transfers.</p>

        <h2>7. Do Not Track (DNT) Signals</h2>
        <p>
          Some browsers support "Do Not Track" (DNT) signals. Currently, there is no universal standard for how websites should respond to DNT signals. We do not currently respond to DNT browser signals, but we respect your cookie preferences set through our cookie consent manager.
        </p>
        <p>
          You have full control over cookies through our consent management platform and browser settings, which we believe provides more granular and meaningful control than DNT signals.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Updates to This Cookie Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time to reflect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Changes in cookie usage or new cookies</li>
          <li>Updates to third-party services and their cookies</li>
          <li>Changes in applicable laws and regulations</li>
          <li>Improvements to our website and services</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Significant changes will be communicated through a prominent notice on our website or via email to registered users. The "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy indicates when it was most recently revised.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Contact Us About Cookies</h2>
        <p>If you have questions or concerns about our use of cookies, please contact us:</p>

        <div class="my-6 p-6 bg-card border border-theme rounded-lg transition-colors">
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors"><strong class="text-primary transition-colors">AUXO Data Labs - Privacy Team</strong></p>
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors">Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@auxodata.com">privacy@auxodata.com</a></p>
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors">General Inquiries: <a href="mailto:hello@auxodata.com">hello@auxodata.com</a></p>
          <p class="!mb-2 text-secondary transition-colors">Location: Dubai, United Arab Emirates</p>
          <p class="!mb-0 text-secondary transition-colors">Contact Form: <a href={createUrl('contact')}>Visit Contact Page</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-8 p-6 bg-lime-400/10 border-l-4 border-lime-400 rounded-r-lg">
          <p class="!mb-0"><strong>Your Privacy Matters:</strong> AUXO Data Labs is committed to transparency in how we use cookies and tracking technologies. We believe in giving you meaningful control over your data and will never use cookies in ways that violate your trust or applicable privacy laws.</p>
        </div>
      </LegalLayout>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
